Description: Saints Anthony Abbot and Paul the Hermit in the wilderness fed by a raven, the bird in the upper left carrying bread in its beak Chiaroscuro woodcut
Curator's comments: The first state of this block (reproduced in 'the Illustrated Bartsch') gives the names of both artists. For the identification of the subject see 1918,0713.11
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
Representation of: St Paul the Hermit
